column5: Headed out to BOQ early yesterday morning ... fished in Trenton ( mouth of the Trent) ... was very slow all day ... a couple guys had a few that they had caught early morning ... finnaly at 5 pm i finnaly get a hit ... missed ... another .... missed ... finnaly hook the little guy (about 3 lbs) .... had a few more hits but the wind started blowin like crazy ... thought my hut was going to collaps ... so I packed it in .... at least I got my first walleye through the ice ... the rest should be easy now
Congrats on popping your cherry, the rest will be alot easier
catching them is a bonus... just getting on the ice is what counts......  wish I could make it down that way this winter.........damn work...
Glad you had some action.Enjoy the eater!
Hey Brit,was that you in the ozark with the wooden floor addition???If so that was me that you talked to.  Bassman
